@Node SP993 "Space -- 1999 > Matter Of Life And Death [#3]"

 @{b}Matter Of Life And Death [#3]@{ub} (1974)
 
 An Eagle returns from a reconnaissance flight to the planet Terra Nova with
 the pilots catatonic and an extra man on board. Helena identifies him as her
 husband, the pilot of Astro 7 lost in the vicinity of Jupiter in 1994.
 
 However, examination of Russell shows peculiarities in his life signs and
 Bergman determines that he is gradually turning into anti-matter. In obvious
 distress, Lee Russell warns the Alphans to stay away from the planet, but is
 unable to explain why. Inexplicably, the man dies and his body disappears.
 Disregarding Russell's warnings, Koenig and Helena lead a landing party to
 Terra Nova where they find a paradise environment, perfect for the Alphans.
 But disaster strikes when the planet apparently turns against them.
 
