@Node SP995 "Space -- 1999 > Ring Around The Moon [#5]"

 @{b}Ring Around The Moon [#5]@{ub} (1974)
 
 Maintenance engineer Ted Clifford is struck by an energy beam which transforms
 his brain into a computer relay station for an alien probe which captures the
 Moon within an energy ring. When Clifford's mind burns out, the probe seeks a
 new relay and a medical mission on the lunar surface provides it with the
 opportunity to capture Helena Russell.
 
 She later returns to Alpha, apparantly unharmed, but is revealed to be
 relaying information from the Alpha computer through an energy implant in
 her brain. In an attempt to free Helena from the probe's control before she
 suffers the same fate as Clifford, Koenig and Carter board the probe and
 discover that the computerised device is on a pre-programmed mission to
 destroy the human race.
 
