@Node SP9941 "Space -- 1999 > Dorzak [#41]"

 @{b}Dorzak [#41]@{ub} (1976)
 
 A Croton spaceship arrives on Alpha and is revealed to contain the Psychon
 philosopher Dorzak imprisoned in stasis. His captor, Sahala, is ferrying him
 to exile on Thesalena, claiming that he incited the Norvahn people to
 violence, but Maya refuses to believe her story as she knows Dorzak as a man
 of peace.
 
 Sahala tells how Dorzak used his mind power on her colleagues, Clea and Yesta,
 leaving Clea dead and Yesta badly injured, but when Yesta recovers she is
 still under Dorzak's influence and accuses Sahala of Clea's murder. On this
 evidence, Verdeschi allows Maya to free Dorzak from stasis and the real
